description:
Appendicitis is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires
prompt medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe
outcomes. Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:
Typhoid is an infectious disease often acquired from vectors or contaminated
food/water. It can cause high fever, body pains and gastrointestinal or systemic
symptoms. Prompt diagnosis and appropriate treatment are important to avoid
complications.
precaution:
Seek prompt medical evaluation and testing; start specific treatment as advised.
Ensure good hydration and follow public health recommendations to prevent
spread.

depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if needed,
investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Stroke is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires prompt
medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:
Dengue is an infectious disease often acquired from vectors or contaminated
food/water. It can cause high fever, body pains and gastrointestinal or systemic
symptoms. Prompt diagnosis and appropriate treatment are important to avoid
complications.
precaution:
Seek prompt medical evaluation and testing; start specific treatment as advised.
Ensure good hydration and follow public health recommendations to prevent
spread.

description:
Bronchitis commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if
needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Flu commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and related
symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

description:
Migraine is a neurological/mental health condition that can significantly affect
quality of life. Symptoms are recurrent and management may include medications
and lifestyle measures. Seek specialist care for persistent or severe symptoms.
precaution:

as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Dengue is an infectious disease often acquired from vectors or contaminated
food/water. It can cause high fever, body pains and gastrointestinal or systemic
symptoms. Prompt diagnosis and appropriate treatment are important to avoid
complications.
precaution:
Seek prompt medical evaluation and testing; start specific treatment as advised.
Ensure good hydration and follow public health recommendations to prevent
spread.

care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if
needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Typhoid is an infectious disease often acquired from vectors or contaminated
food/water. It can cause high fever, body pains and gastrointestinal or systemic
symptoms. Prompt diagnosis and appropriate treatment are important to avoid
complications.
precaution:
Seek prompt medical evaluation and testing; start specific treatment as advised.
Ensure good hydration and follow public health recommendations to prevent
spread.

description:
Flu commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and related
symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

description:
Heat Stroke is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires prompt
medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

prompt medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe
outcomes. Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:
Chickenpox causes characteristic symptoms and may require medical or supportive
care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if
needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Pneumonia commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if
needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Sprain is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires prompt
medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Immobilize the affected area and seek orthopedic or urgent care evaluation.
Follow recommended imaging and treatment plans.

description:

medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:

description:
Common Cold commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes

medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:
COVID-19 commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

food/water. It can cause high fever, body pains and gastrointestinal or systemic
symptoms. Prompt diagnosis and appropriate treatment are important to avoid
complications.
precaution:
Seek prompt medical evaluation and testing; start specific treatment as advised.
Ensure good hydration and follow public health recommendations to prevent
spread.

description:
Acne causes characteristic symptoms and may require medical or supportive care
depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation and, if needed,

precaution:

description:
Hypertension is a chronic medical condition that affects metabolic or
circulatory systems. It requires medical evaluation and long-term management to
prevent complications. Regular monitoring and adherence to treatment plans are
essential.
precaution:
Follow prescribed medication and lifestyle advice; attend regular follow-up and
monitoring. Seek medical review for uncontrolled symptoms or complications.

description:
Heart Attack is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires

outcomes. Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.

description:
COVID-19 commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe

supportive care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation
and, if needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:

as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Common Cold commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

description:

supportive care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation
and, if needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Flu commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and related
symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

supportive care depending on severity. Diagnosis is based on clinical evaluation
and, if needed, investigations. Follow medical advice for appropriate treatment.
precaution:
Seek medical advice if symptoms persist or worsen; use supportive care measures
as appropriate. Follow prevention and hygiene measures to reduce risk.

description:
Stroke is a potentially serious or emergency condition that requires prompt
medical attention. Early recognition and treatment can prevent severe outcomes.
Do not delay seeking emergency care when signs are present.
precaution:
Call emergency services or go to the nearest hospital immediately; do not wait.
Follow emergency care instructions and avoid oral intake if surgery may be
required.

description:
Bronchitis commonly affects the respiratory system causing cough, fever and
related symptoms. Severity varies and the illness can range from mild to severe
depending on the cause and host factors. Seek care if breathing becomes
difficult or symptoms worsen.
precaution:
Rest, stay hydrated and use over-the-counter medications for symptom relief.
Isolate if contagious and seek care if breathing difficulty or high fever
occurs.

description:

precaution:

Follow recommended imaging and treatment plans.
